OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1779494576
OL,3,CChildren 'more likely than working-age
OL,4,Cadults to live in private rented
OL,5,Csector'
OL,7,FThe foundation said that a lack of
OL,8,Fsecurity for young families in
OL,9,Fparticular underlines why the rights
OL,10,Fenshrined in the Renters' Rights Act
OL,11,F2025, which recently came into force
OL,12,Fin England, are needed.
OL,14,FThe Act signals the end of Section 21
OL,15,F"no fault" evictions, meaning private
OL,16,Flandlords will not be able to evict
OL,17,Ftenants without a valid justification.
OL,19,FLandlords must also reasonably
OL,20,Fconsider renters' requests to live
OL,21,Fwith a pet.
OL,26,@wD@AOUwD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
