CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1779494576
OL,3,CChildren 'more likely than working-age
OL,4,Cadults to live in private rented
OL,5,Csector'
OL,7,F"The Renters' Rights Act will
OL,8,Falleviate some of these concerns by
OL,9,Fsetting minimum property standards and
OL,10,Foffering more security."
OL,12,FA Ministry of Housing, Communities and
OL,13,FLocal Government spokesperson said:
OL,14,F"The Renters' Rights Act brings the
OL,15,Fbiggest reforms to renting in over 40
OL,16,Fyears, with significant protections
OL,17,Fnow in force to support renting
OL,18,Ffamilies.
OL,26,@oD@AOUrD@XO]vD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
